#Function Name: NETdataclean
#Description: take dataframe as parameter, returns cleaned dataframe with NET Tool columns.

def NETdataclean(df):
    seeds = pd.read_csv("MNCAATourneySeeds.csv")
    seeds = seeds[seeds.Season > 2015]
    seeds['Region'] = seeds['Seed'].str[0]
    #Score Margin
    df["Score_Margin"] = df["WScore"]-df["LScore"]
#     print("Proportion of Score Margin over 10: ", (df[df["Score Margin"]>=10].count()["Score Margin"])\
#           /df["Score Margin"].count())
    
    #Net Efficiency
    df["WPossession"] =  df["WTO"]+df["WFGA"]+0.475*df["WFTM"]-df["WOR"]
    df["WEfficiency"] = df["WScore"] / df["WPossession"]

    df["LPossession"] = df["LTO"]+df["LFGA"]+0.475*df["LFTM"]-df["LOR"]
    df["LEfficiency"] = df["LScore"] / df["LPossession"]

    df["NetEfficiency"] = df["WEfficiency"] - df["LEfficiency"]
    
    df['WFGP'] = df.WFGM / df.WFGA
    df['WFG3P'] = df.WFGM3 / df.WFGA3
    df['WFTMP'] = df.WFTM / df.WFTA
    
    df['LLoc'] = [('A' if x == 'H' else('H' if x == 'A' else 'N')) for x in df["WLoc"]]
    df['AdjW'] = [(1.4 if x == 'A' else(1.0 if x == 'N' else 0.6)) for x in df['WLoc']]
    df['AdjL'] = [(-1.4 if x == 'H' else(-1.0 if x == 'N' else -0.6)) for x in df['LLoc']]

    
    seeds["Seednum"] = seeds["Seed"].map(lambda x: x.lstrip('0WXYZ').rstrip('ab'))
    
    test1 = pd.merge(df[["WTeamID",'Season']],seeds, left_on=['WTeamID', 'Season'],\
                 right_on = ['TeamID', 'Season'], validate = 'many_to_many')
    test2 = pd.merge(df[["LTeamID",'Season']],seeds, left_on = ['LTeamID', 'Season'], \
                 right_on = ['TeamID', 'Season'], validate = 'many_to_many')
    test1 = test1.drop(['TeamID','Season','WTeamID'], axis = 1)\
    .rename(columns = {'Seednum': 'WSeednum', 'Seed':'WSeed'})
    test2 = test2.drop(['TeamID','Season', 'LTeamID'], axis = 1)\
    .rename(columns = {'Seednum': 'LSeednum', 'Seed':'LSeed'})

    seednum = pd.concat([test1,test2], axis = 1)
    df = df.reset_index().drop(columns= 'index')
    cleaneddf = pd.concat([df, seednum], axis = 1)
#     cleaneddf.dropna(inplace = True)
#     cleaneddf.WSeednum = cleaneddf.WSeednum.astype('int32')

    return cleaneddf

# Win Rank Function
# Description: accepts results csv file as parameter and returns
# gamecount dataframe with win/lose count, total num of games, and respective team names. 

def gamecount(df):
    win_count = pd.DataFrame(df["WTeamID"].value_counts()).reset_index()
    win_count.rename(columns = {'index':'WTeamID', 'WTeamID':'Wcount'}, inplace = True)
    lose_count = pd.DataFrame(df["LTeamID"].value_counts()).reset_index()
    lose_count.rename(columns = {'index':'LTeamID', 'LTeamID':'Lcount'}, inplace = True)
    
    count = pd.concat([win_count, lose_count], axis = 1)
    winid = list(count['WTeamID'].unique())
    loseid = list(count['LTeamID'].unique())
    cleaned = []
    for i in loseid:
        if i not in winid:
            cleaned.append(i)
    for i in range(len(cleaned)):
        count['WTeamID'].fillna(cleaned[i],limit = 1,inplace = True)

    count['Wcount'].fillna(0, inplace = True)
    win = count.iloc[:,:2]
    lose = count.iloc[:,2:]

    cleaned = pd.merge(win, lose, left_on = 'WTeamID', right_on = 'LTeamID', validate = 'one_to_one')
    cleaned.drop(columns = 'LTeamID', axis = 1, inplace = True)
    cleaned.rename(columns = {'WTeamID':'TeamID'}, inplace = True)

    cleaned['TotalGames'] = cleaned.Wcount + cleaned.Lcount
    cleaned = cleaned.astype('int32')
    cleaned['Winning_Percentage'] = cleaned.Wcount / cleaned.TotalGames
    
    teamname = pd.read_csv('MTeams.csv')
#     tempmerge = pd.merge(teamname, seeds[['TeamID','Region']], on = 'TeamID')
    
#     seeds = pd.read_csv("MNCAATourneySeeds.csv")
#     seeds["Seednum"] = seeds["Seed"].map(lambda x: x.lstrip('0WXYZ').rstrip('ab'))
    
#     tempmerge = pd.merge(cleaned, teamname[['TeamID', 'TeamName']], on = 'TeamID')
#     print(tempmerge)
    gamecount = pd.merge(cleaned, teamname[['TeamID','TeamName']], on = 'TeamID')
    gamecount = gamecount[['TeamID','TeamName','Wcount','Lcount','TotalGames','Winning_Percentage']]
    return gamecount

def cinfilter(df, teamID):
    Wcinderella = df[df.WTeamID == teamID]
    Lcinderella = df[df.LTeamID == teamID]
    
    cind = Wcinderella.append(Lcinderella)
    cind = cind.loc[cind.EventTeamID == teamID]
    return cind

**The king, the jester, and the… Cinderella?**

> 	We wanted to observe how the teams played: we divided the team by 3 groups - the kings (teams that have made the finals), the jesters (teams that have lost on their first game on the tournaments), and the cinderella (teams that were viewed as underdogs, but have outperformed their expectations. For the cinderellas, we have identified Gonzaga for 2016, Xavier for 2017, and Syracuse and Loyola for 2018 based on the  NCAA article (https://www.ncaa.com/news/basketball-men/2019-03-06/march-madness-three-traits-cinderella-must-have).
> 	Looking at the action types, we were able to see one consistent trend: both the rebound and the field goal attempts were consistently higher for the kings and the cinderellas. We believe that this was a material factor in deciding the performance of the teams.
